args:
Emile awakens a special dormant android
called Mascula to chase down the prince.
But instead of doing so, Mascula steals the
weapons of friend and foe alike and runs off.
Let no foe through! Solidify defenses in\nthe rearguard and prioritize the escape\nof children and the elderly!
And let's put some distance between us\nand the imperial army while we can.
Yeah, if they show up again, things\ncould get pretty hairy pretty quick.
Cleo said our foes are called ＂androids＂?
It rhymes with ＂annoyed,＂ which is\ntotally what they're making me!
Androids are weapons created by the\nDyrenell Empire some 300 years ago\nin order to slay dragons.
I take it they are not actually human\ndespite all outside appearances?
Correct. I am not especially knowledgeable\non the subject, but apparently they are\na type of magical weapon.

Androids do not grow tired or feel pain.
They are soulless soldiers whose only
purpose is to carry out the orders of
the one who commands them.
This is a lot to take in.
Here I was all ready to rail on androids,\nand now I kinda feel sorry for 'em.
They're not an enemy soft enough\nfor us to afford sympathy.
Yeah, best not to have any illusions here.\nWe ain't fightin' men or even fiends.\nThese things are just...things.
I don't like reducing our enemy to a\n＂thing,＂ but I suppose that may be\nwhat we have to do to win this fight.
Regardless, our first priority has to be\ngetting the villagers to safety.

Aaah ha ha! How did I know I'd find you
idiots standing around debating morality
instead of doing the smart thing and
running away?!
It is indeed! And today, my dear brother,\nis the day you finally meet your doom!

No mercy! No quarter! As your final breath
escapes your pathetic, shattered form,
you will know that I—the mighty Emile—
have been the instrument of your demise!
That's rich, considering we've been the\nones sparing YOUR life over and over!

The weakest dog barks loudest, dragon!
But since you clearly lack the faculties to
grasp the situation you find yourself in,
permit me to enlighten you.
Dammit, I hate these stupid things!\nI can't read their movements at all!

They are utterly removed of emotion,
or any discernible rhythm. We cannot
approach them like typical human
opponents.
Yeah... Guess we'll have to wing it.
We cannot allow them to pass,\nor they will slaughter all of the\nvillagers to a man, woman, and child.
We can't hold these guys off forever.\nWe gotta speed up the evacuation!
We're trying to clear out a village with\nold folks and kids, Luca! It's not exactly\nthe quickest process in the world!
J-just hold out a little longer,\neveryone!
Aaaaah ha ha ha! Look at those fools!\nLook how delightfully desperate they are\nwhen scurrying to and fro!

Truly, this is the natural order of things.
The superior being—me—has taken
charge of the lesser. But alas, it is time
for this pathetic display to come to an end.
Soldiers! Bring me my special androids!
According to Chelle, these two are even\nstronger than the rest of their kind.

They're also apparently quite the handful,
which is why they have been kept dormant.
But no willful android can stand against
the might and majesty of Emile!
Let's start with this one, shall we?\nAwaken, my killing machine!

Checking condition.
Condition clear.
Checking Orchis System.
System clear.
Very well, Mascula! I order you to kill\nevery single one of those miserable,\nscurrying wretches over there!
Seconds elapsed: 9,445,032,000...\nAnd even now, the fighting continues...
Hey! You there! Do less...whatever it is\nthat you're doing and start killing already!
I will not fight.\nAnd I will not let anyone else fight, either!
We need a new plan here, guys!\nThese androids just keep comin'!
Enough, my brethren. There is no longer\nany need for us to fight.
You are an obstacle to this operation.\nCommencing elimination.
Then I have no other choice.

I disabled the part of it that receives
orders from the one who wields the
control element. It will be immobile
for some time.
Wait, so you saved us?\nBut you're an android!
Androids do not wish to fight.\nI'm sure no one really does.\nDon't you agree?
Uh...yeah, I guess so? I mean,\nfighting's really just a last resort.
Exactly.\nSo please hand over your weapons.
You fight because you have weapons.\nTherefore, we must get rid of weapons.\nPlease give them to me.
Look, friend, we can't just hand over all\nour weapons in the middle of a—HEY!
Okay, what the heck's up with HIM?\nThat was awful...
Hey, Ranzal. Man, did you see what that...\nUh, wait. Where'd your axe go?
Funny story—some weird android came\nracin' by and yanked it outta my hand.
I got no idea WHAT that's about.

Yeah, he was sayin' a bunch of stuff about
not wanting to fight or have us fight.
I think he did the same thing to all
the imperials, too.
So he's a pacifist, then?\nThere are pacifistic androids?
Well, in any case, this will allow us to put\nsome miles between us and the imperials.\nLet's retreat while we still can!
WHAT DID THAT BUCKET OF BOLTS DO?!

That stupid android took matters into his
own pathetic hands, which allowed my
brother and his bothersome band of
bloviators to escape me yet again!
Someone bring me my pathetic brother\nso I can kill him with my own two hands!
